285
00:18:57,799 --> 00:19:00,599
They seem to be inside the other packages too!

286
00:19:00,599 --> 00:19:02,699
-What? -Look.

287
00:19:10,299 --> 00:19:13,599
Certainly, the date shown on the receipt

288
00:19:13,599 --> 00:19:16,799
and the date on the courier invoice match,

289
00:19:16,799 --> 00:19:19,599
so we can tell that it was sent the same day it was bought.

290
00:19:19,599 --> 00:19:21,399
Since the receipt is ripped,

291
00:19:21,399 --> 00:19:23,899
it's impossible to tell where the item was bought.

292
00:19:23,899 --> 00:19:26,799
But something is in view only on the receipt

293
00:19:26,799 --> 00:19:29,099
for the T-shirts bought last week.

294
00:19:29,099 --> 00:19:30,999
See, it wasn't ripped off clean enough,

295
00:19:30,999 --> 00:19:33,799
so a mark of something is in view.

296
00:19:33,799 --> 00:19:37,099
This is...

297
00:19:37,099 --> 00:19:39,899
It's the mark of the Beika Department Store here!

298
00:19:39,899 --> 00:19:43,499
Besides, doesn't it bother you that all the items were

299
00:19:43,499 --> 00:19:47,299
bought at the same time, 12:28 pm?

300
00:19:50,599 --> 00:19:53,499
I see! That's why the bomb man

301
00:19:53,499 --> 00:19:57,199
is so sure that the sender is on this floor!

302
00:19:57,199 --> 00:19:58,299
Because he found out that the sender

303
00:19:58,299 --> 00:20:02,199
was buying the T-shirts here afternoon!

304
00:20:02,199 --> 00:20:03,599
Wait a sec.

305
00:20:03,599 --> 00:20:06,999
But why is this sports item floor?

306
00:20:06,999 --> 00:20:10,599
Maybe because this T-shirt is an underwear?

307
00:20:10,599 --> 00:20:13,799
"Underwear" -It's written on the receipt too.

308
00:20:13,799 --> 00:20:17,099
You know, it's a polyester wear that is worn

309
00:20:17,099 --> 00:20:21,099
when jogging that sucks up perspiration and dries quickly!

310
00:20:21,099 --> 00:20:22,799
I get it!

311
00:20:22,799 --> 00:20:25,899
Do you know where this is sold?

312
00:20:25,899 --> 00:20:29,299
I think it's sold in the fitness wear section.

313
00:20:30,299 --> 00:20:31,999
Please take us there!

314
00:20:31,999 --> 00:20:34,299
Yes, sir. This way.

315
00:20:40,299 --> 00:20:41,699
Strange.

316
00:20:41,699 --> 00:20:43,999
The receipts till two weeks ago are torn,

317
00:20:43,999 --> 00:20:46,599
so you can't tell where the items were bought.

318
00:20:46,599 --> 00:20:49,299
Why did the sender make such a mistake just this week.

319
00:20:49,299 --> 00:20:50,799
Besides...

320
00:20:54,099 --> 00:20:55,999
What's the matter, Conan?

321
00:20:55,999 --> 00:20:57,899
Did you notice something again?

322
00:20:57,899 --> 00:20:59,399
Oh, yes...

323
00:20:59,399 --> 00:21:01,999
I was thinking that this receipt is strange.

324
00:21:01,999 --> 00:21:03,099
Strange?

325
00:21:03,099 --> 00:21:04,499
Because... Look.

326
00:21:04,499 --> 00:21:06,499
If the sender wanted to hide the place,

327
00:21:06,499 --> 00:21:08,999
he could've just torn off the upper left part,

328
00:21:08,999 --> 00:21:11,599
but the upper right part is torn off too.

329
00:21:11,599 --> 00:21:14,399
Maybe this person is just not too reliable?

330
00:21:14,399 --> 00:21:16,799
Even the T-shirts are folded messily.

331
00:21:16,799 --> 00:21:19,899
-What? The way they're folded? -Yes.

332
00:21:22,599 --> 00:21:28,099
See! There's a strange crease on this one T-shirt.

333
00:21:28,099 --> 00:21:31,399
If you fold this T-shirt, according to the crease...

334
00:21:31,399 --> 00:21:33,699
This is how it looks.

335
00:21:35,399 --> 00:21:37,999
This is...

336
00:21:37,999 --> 00:21:39,699
Couldn't it be...

337
00:21:44,299 --> 00:21:46,999
What shall we do? Shall we force entry?

338
00:21:46,999 --> 00:21:48,699
No, wait.

339
00:21:48,699 --> 00:21:51,699
It seems that the bomb man said that if the police approach,

340
00:21:51,699 --> 00:21:54,499
he would set the bomb off.

341
00:21:54,499 --> 00:21:55,899
But...

342
00:21:55,899 --> 00:21:58,199
According to the informant, the bombs are...

343
00:21:58,199 --> 00:22:00,199
We can't rely on that information.

344
00:22:00,199 --> 00:22:04,199
They may have said that just because they want to be safe.

345
00:22:04,199 --> 00:22:06,599
We've got no choice now but to wait

346
00:22:06,599 --> 00:22:09,099
for the bomb man to make his move.

347
00:22:11,899 --> 00:22:13,199
Hey.

348
00:22:13,199 --> 00:22:16,299
How long do I have to wait?

349
00:22:16,299 --> 00:22:19,199
For a phantom that's not even around.

350
00:22:19,199 --> 00:22:21,499
Hold horses, Chianti.

351
00:22:21,499 --> 00:22:23,499
The info we got of a man who resembles Akai,

352
00:22:23,499 --> 00:22:26,899
is going into the department store is certain.

353
00:22:26,899 --> 00:22:28,799
I'm going to check with my own eyes

354
00:22:28,799 --> 00:22:32,499
whether that guy is really a phantom or not.

355
00:22:32,499 --> 00:22:35,599
If it turns out that he isn't a phantom,

356
00:22:35,599 --> 00:22:37,799
in that exact moment,

357
00:22:37,799 --> 00:22:41,599
you're going to become a phantom.

358
00:22:41,599 --> 00:22:43,099
Kir.

359
00:24:04,699 --> 00:24:08,399
Transform!

360
00:24:08,399 --> 00:24:11,799
I'm so overjoyed I can't contain it.

361
00:24:11,799 --> 00:24:14,899
Because then, I could kill him all over again.

362
00:24:16,699 --> 00:24:20,599
Wait, Dad. That's right near the bomb.

363
00:24:20,599 --> 00:24:23,199
I won't allow the bombs to explode.

